headlines.description: Tra Holder scored 29 points on 8-for-16 shooting, and No. 16 Arizona State pulled off a 95-85 upset of No. 2 Kansas on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Holder leads No. 16 Arizona State to upset over No. 2 Kansas

headlines.description: Phil Booth and Donte DiVincenzo each scored 18 points to help No. 4 Villanova avoid an upset and remain undefeated in a 77-68 win over La Salle on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: DiVincenzo, Booth rally No. 4 Villanova past La Salle 77-68

video.headline: Villanova remains undefeated with win vs. La Salle

headlines.description: Johnathan Williams had 23 points and 12 rebounds, Zach Norvell Jr. added 21 points and No. 12 Gonzaga ran away in the second half for a 97-70 win over Washington on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Williams leads No. 12 Gonzaga to 97-70 rout of Washington

headlines.description: Carsen Edwards scored a career-high 27 points and No. 21 Purdue beat IUPUI 86-61 on Sunday night for coach Matt Painter's 300th victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 21 Purdue beats IUPUI for Painter's 300th victory

headlines.description: Braian Angola had 18 points and eight rebounds to lead Florida State to a 72-53 win over Tulane on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Angola scores 18, Florida State defeats Tulane 72-53

headlines.description: Gerdarius Troutman scored 20 points and Justin Massey 16, both hitting four 3-pointers, and Florida Atlantic threatened the school scoring record with a 108-46 win over NAIA Webber International on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: FAU has 3rd highest score in 108-46 win over Webber Int

headlines.description: Rodney Chatman scored 23 points and made seven of eight free throws and Chattanooga beat Charlotte 64-50 on Sunday for the 49ers' fourth straight loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Chattanooga beats Charlotte 64-50 behind Chatman's 23 points

headlines.description: Shawn Anderson scored 21 points and grabbed 12 rebounds for his first double-double and Navy rallied in the second half on Sunday to edge Columbia 73-68 for its fifth-straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anderson rallies Navy to 73-68 win over Columbia

headlines.description: Bo Hodges scored 18 points with 8-for-9 shooting to lead East Tennessee State to a 94-48 win over Hiawassee College on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: ETSU overpowers Hiwassee College 94-48

headlines.description: Matt Mooney scored 19 points, including nine in the final 2:37 of the game, to help South Dakota hold off Eastern Washington 75-73 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: South Dakota holds off Eastern Washington 75-73

headlines.description: Mike Laster scored 23 points and all five of his free throws, Kevin Mickle added 17 points, and Ohio held off a late Western Kentucky run to win 89-84 on Sunday, ending the Hilltoppers' three-game win streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ohio holds off W Kentucky 89-84 behind Laster's 23 points

headlines.description: Joe Chealy scored 20 points with four 3-pointers and five assist as Charleston defeated Division II North Greenville 92-60 on Sunday to run its winning streak to five.
headlines.shortLinkText: Chealy scores 20, Charleston beats D-II N Greenville 92-60

headlines.description: Dachon Burke scored 25 points with six 3-pointers and Robert Morris made 11 from beyond the arc in beating Drexel 74-60 on Sunday to end the Dragons' three-game win streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Burke scores 25, Robert Morris beats Drexel 74-60

headlines.description: Jamaal King scored 26 points, including the go-ahead 3-pointer in overtime, Keith Braxton added 24 points to go with 12 rebounds and St. Francis (Pa.) edged past Niagara for a 93-87 win Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: St. Francis (PA) edges Niagara in overtime 93-87

headlines.description: Duson Majstorovic and Isaiah White each scored 20 points and provided the force as Maine celebrated Star Wars Day with a 104-51 trouncing of Division III University of Maine at Machias on Sunday afternoon.
headlines.shortLinkText: Maine Black Bears maul in-state rival Maine-Machias, 104-51

headlines.description: Cliff Thomas Jr. scored 16 points and led a 68-point effort by the High Point bench as the Panthers celebrated the holidays by pummeling Division II Toccoa Falls College, 110-39 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: High Point celebrates while pummeling Toccoa Falls, 110-39

headlines.description: Chris Clarke scored a season-best 18 points to carry Virginia Tech to a 93-40 victory over Maryland Eastern Shore on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clarke, Hokies bury Maryland Eastern Shore 93-40

headlines.description: Jalen Henry poured in a season-high 26 points, including two free throws with three seconds left in the game, and SIU Edwardsville rallied to beat South Alabama 76-75.
headlines.shortLinkText: Henry lifts SIU-Edwardsville over South Alabama 76-75

headlines.description: Dominic Magee scored 27 points, Tyree Griffin added a career-high 23 with five assists, and Southern Miss beat Troy 89-71 on Sunday after winning the turnover battle for the ninth time this season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Southern Miss beats Troy; Person hits 300th 3

headlines.description: Fatodd Lewis poured in a career-high 34 points, grabbed 16 rebounds and had 12 assists for his first triple-double and UT Martin defeated Cincinnati Clermont 127-92 on Sunday in a game where 3-pointers were flying.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fatodd triple-double, UT Martin lights up scoreboard 127-92

headlines.description: Jerome Segura scored 14 points on 7-of-9 shooting and handed out six assists to help Fairfield turn back LIU Brooklyn 76-72 on Sunday to snap a three-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fairfield tops LIU Brooklyn 76-72 to end three-game slide

headlines.description: Raekwon Miller hit 4 of 6 3-point attempts and led North Carolina-Asheville with 19 points as the Bulldogs overwhelmed the Buffaloes of NAIA member Milligan College, 97-60 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Miller's 19 points leads UNC Asheville past Milligan, 97-60

headlines.description: Emmanuel Nzekwesi scored 17 points, Javan White added 14, and Oral Roberts rallied to beat Missouri State 73-66 on Sunday to end the Bears' seven-game win streak and tie the series 8-8.
headlines.shortLinkText: Oral Roberts ends Missouri St 7-game streak with 73-66 win

headlines.description: Blake Francis scored 19 points, got seven steals and dished out five assists Sunday to help propel Wagner to its sixth-straight win with a 75-41 victory over Division II program Mercy College.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wagner cruises past Mercy for 75-41 win

headlines.description: Freshman Luka Garza had 23 points and 13 rebounds to help Iowa snap a four-game skid with a 91-60 win over Southern on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Garza has 23 points, 13 rebounds; Iowa beats Southern 91-60

headlines.description: Duop Reath scored a career-high 30 points and Tremont Waters added 20 as LSU beat UNC Wilmington 97-84 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Reath scores career-high 30; LSU beats UNC Wilmington 97-84

headlines.description: Donovan Jackson scored 25 points, including a career-high seven 3s, Cameron Lard had 15 points with 11 rebounds and Iowa State held off Alcorn State 78-58 on Sunday for its seventh straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sluggish Cyclones hold off Alcorn State 78-58

headlines.description: Drew McDonald and Carson Williams combined to score 44 points and Northern Kentucky topped Eastern Kentucky 91-63 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Northern Kentucky tops in-state rival Eastern Kentucky 91-63

headlines.description: Freshman Jalen Sanders had 17 of his career-high 21 points in the first half, Andre Spight finished with 20 points, five rebounds and five assists and Northern Colorado cruised to a 104-53 win over Division II Panhandle State on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sanders, Spight lead Northern Colorado past Panhandle State

nowFeed.headline: Under Sean Miller Deandre Ayton is maximizing his enormous potential. Ayton has always possessed the physical tools and a solid basketball IQ. He has worked hard at Zona along with making the adjustments to college basketball. For a freshman big man it's really hard to dominate right away. Since he arrived in the states he was a top ranked player in his class. Would have been top 5 in last years NBA draft. Now he will be a top 3 pick and will be much more prepared.

nowFeed.headline: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

nowFeed.headline: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.
